Subject: [PATCH] aarch64-mingw: disable libbid binary80 helpers

For aarch64-w64-mingw32, long double is 64 bits and libgcc does not
provide XFmode or TFmode support. libbid still enables its binary80
conversion helpers by default, then treats long double as an 80-bit
layout. When building with -Werror this trips an uninitialized read
in bid_binarydecimal.c, and the generated helpers would not describe
the target ABI anyway.

Keep this target-specific to the libgcc build by defining the existing
libbid guard from the aarch64 MinGW tmake fragment.

--- a/libgcc/config/aarch64/t-mingw
+++ b/libgcc/config/aarch64/t-mingw
@@ -1,2 +1,3 @@
 # Bypass hidden attribute warnings in MinGW until it is implemented
 LIBGCC2_CFLAGS += -Wno-error=attributes
+LIBGCC2_CFLAGS += -D__NO_BINARY80__
